{"questionId":"27802","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Kacheena stands at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>K</mtext></math>, the top of a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>218</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> vertical cliff. The base of the cliff is located at&nbsp;point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>. A ship is located at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>S</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1200</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> from Kacheena.</p>\n<p>This information is shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/89c3edbf035c9a48ef01daea716db678000eb045.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the horizontal distance from the base of the cliff to the ship.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>SB</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>218</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>1200</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4468</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>SB</mtext><mn>1200</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4468</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>218</mn><mtext>SB</mtext></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mtext>BS</mtext><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>79</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5331</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1200</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1180</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mtext>m</mtext></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>1392476</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1180</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27802","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.1b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the horizontal distance from the base of the cliff to the ship.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}